<HEADLINE> Republicans Raise $9.5M in March  </HEADLINE>
By JONATHAN D. SALANT, Associated Press Writer
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- The Republican Party raised $9.5 million in
March -- its best fund-raising month this year -- as it continues to
pad its war chest for the fall campaign.
</P>
<P>
   Finance Chairman Mel Sembler said donors were focusing on the
November general election now that George W. Bush is the party's
likely presidential nominee.
</P>
<P>
   ''Republicans are energized,'' Sembler said Thursday. ''They're
enthusiastic that the primaries are now behind us and we're all
pulling together.''
</P>
<P>
   Some of that enthusiasm will help the party surpass the March
total in a single night in April, when its annual gala will bring
in a record-shattering $15 million. Bush is the headliner for the
April 26 black-tie event. Six-figure donors will be able to attend
a private reception with the Texas governor before the fund-raising
dinner.
</P>
<P>
   The March fund-raising will boost the size of the RNC's bank
account, which had at $20 million at the beginning of the month. In
comparison, the Democratic National Committee had less than $6
million on hand when it last disclosed its finances at the end of
December.
</P>
<P>
   Updated fund-raising figures are due at the Federal Election
Commission in mid-April.
</P>
<P>
   Republican Party officials plan to spend $20 million on issue
advertisements in support of Republican candidates and another
$13.7 million to help elect Bush, Sembler said.
</P>
<P>
   Overall, the Republican National Committee raised $26 million
during the first three months of the year toward a year-end goal of
$177 million.
</P>
<P>
   The GOP's effort soon will get a boost when some of Bush's top
fund-raisers join the party apparatus. In addition, the Texas
governor is still raising money for his presidential campaign,
taking in $2.7 million in the last two weeks. Bush has shattered
all fund-raising records by pulling in more than $75 million for
his campaign.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
