<HEADLINE> Dow Climbs 79; Nasdaq Jumps 91  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- The Dow Jones industrial average is up 79 points
in today's early going. Advancing issues on the New York Stock
Exchange hold a 7-4 lead over decliners.
</P>
<P>
   The Nasdaq Composite Index is ahead 91 points and the Standard &AMP;
Poor's 500 Stock Index is up 12 points.
</P>
<P>
   Wall Street will see if it can keep the Nasdaq's losing streak
to just four sessions.
</P>
<P>
   The technology-dominated index has sold off each day this week,
with sharp declines the past three sessions.
</P>
<P>
   Analysts say many investors have decided to sell some of their
high-tech holdings, locking in dramatic gains that have been
realized already this year.
</P>
<P>
   That selling has sent the Nasdaq nearly 12 percent below its
March tenth closing high.
</P>
<P>
   Some market-watchers say this week's selling, as nerve-wracking
as it has been, was needed to clean out some of the market's
excesses.
</P>
