<HEADLINE> Illinois Grad Students Stage Sit-In  </HEADLINE>
By JOHN KELLY, Associated Press Writer
<TEXT>
<P>
   URBANA, Ill. (AP) -- Graduate students trying to win recognition
for a union ended a 20-hour sit-in at the University of Illinois
administration building Friday, saying their next step could be a
strike.
</P>
<P>
   About 50 protesters walked out of the building chanting: ''We
keep this campus open, we can shut it down.''
</P>
<P>
   A university spokesman said the demonstrations will not change
the school's anti-union stance.
</P>
<P>
   Thousands of graduate students do research, fill administrative
jobs and teach about half of the entry-level classes on campus. In
exchange, they get free tuition and stipends that administrators
say increased at a higher rate than inflation since 1990.
</P>
<P>
   The Graduate Employees Organization is demanding better working
conditions, pay and benefits.
</P>
<P>
   The group will meet April 10, and ''can't not consider'' a
strike, GEO leader David Kamper said.
</P>
<P>
   According to the Chronicle of Higher Education, 27 campuses had
recognized graduate student unions by December, and organizing
efforts were under way at many other schools.
</P>
<P>
   The Illinois sit-in began Thursday when students, labor
activists and ministers refused to leave the administration offices
until they were granted a meeting with administrators. The request
was denied.
</P>
<P>
   The students left the following morning, saying they had made
their point.
</P>
<P>
   The protest followed two days of demonstrations and rallies on
campus with graduate students teaching classes on the lawn and
grading homework in hallways to show the work they do.
</P>
<P>
   ''We feel underpaid for our jobs,'' said graduate employee
Theresa Ferguson. ''I work many more hours than I get paid for, but
I have no rights to give the administration my input about my
working conditions.''
</P>
<P>
   University spokesman Bill Murphy said the school isn't satisfied
with the pay levels but has limited funds to work with.
</P>
<P>
   ------
</P>
<P>
   On the Net:
</P>
<P>
   University of Illinois: http://www.uiuc.edu
</P>
<P>
   Graduate Employees Organization: www.shout.net/(tilde)geo
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
