<HEADLINE> AP Financial News at 3:10 p.m. EST  </HEADLINE>
Friday, March 31, 2000
<TEXT>
<P>
   Prognosis Is Dim for DrKoop.com
</P>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Shares of the Internet health company DrKoop.com
Inc. plunged more than 40 percent today after the company's
accountant said the Internet firm may not survive. In the company's
annual report filed late Thursday with the Securities and Exchange
Commission, PricewaterhouseCoopers LLC said Drkoop.com has
sustained losses and negative cash flows from operations since its
inception. And the auditor expressed ''substantial doubt'' about
the company's ability to continue as a going concern. Such warnings
are extremely rare in the world of public companies, and auditors
only use such terms if they believe the company has a good chance
of going out of business within the year. Koop stock was down 2} at
3{ in afternoon trading.
</P>
<P>
   Nasdaq Up 126.61; Dow Up 75.08
</P>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks turned mostly higher today as investors
shook off their distress over plummeting technology shares and
began looking for bargains after a weeklong selloff. Just before 3
p.m. EST, the Nasdaq composite index was up 126.61 at 4,584.50
after dropping 187 points yesterday. The index had been lower for
most of the morning. The Dow Jones industrial average was up 75.08
at 11,055.33. The Nasdaq began moving higher on the strength of
stalwarts like Dell Computer, up 2} at 54 15/16, and Intel, up 6
5/16 at 133 5/16.
</P>
