</P>
<P>
   PARIS (AP) -- Engineering group Alstom is buying Asea Brown
Boveri's stake in their power generation joint venture for $1.2
billion with a goal of making Alstom one of the world's biggest
power equipment makers. Anglo-French Alstom said today it has
agreed to buy Swiss-Swedish ABB's 50 percent stake in ABB Alstom
Power, to be renamed Alstom Power. Alstom Chairman Pierre Bilger
said the deal would boost his firm's earnings by 15 percent per
year. A previous forecast had seen earnings growth of 6 percent.
</P>
