<HEADLINE> Princess-Prowler's Charges Dropped  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LONDON (AP) -- Harassment charges were dropped Friday against a
man arrested last month outside Princess Anne's country home.
</P>
<P>
   Bernard Quinn, 57, had always denied accusations that he
harassed police by repeatedly trying to enter Anne's estate in
southwest England.
</P>
<P>
   He reportedly was obsessed with the 49-year-old daughter of
Queen Elizabeth II.
</P>
<P>
   Authorities said when Quinn was arrested and charged, they
thought they had enough evidence to prosecute him.
</P>
<P>
   ''However, this view is not shared by the Crown Prosecution
Service, which has decided to discontinue proceedings against Mr.
Quinn,'' said Superintendent Adrian Grimmitt of the Gloucestershire
Police.
</P>
<P>
   After Quinn's brief hearing Friday, he told reporters that his
''name has been blazoned over the headlines and that clearly wasn't
right.'' He refused to comment further.
</P>
<P>
   Buckingham Palace had no comment.
</P>
