<HEADLINE> Larry Flynt To Open Adult Bookstore  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   CINCINNATI (AP) -- Hustler magazine publisher Larry Flynt
promised to find another downtown location for his adult bookstore
after it was closed last year. Now it appears he's keeping that
promise.
</P>
<P>
   Flynt said Thursday he and his brother would open a new downtown
store within a week.
</P>
<P>
   The store will sell some sexually explicit material, but he said
most of the merchandise will be mainstream items such as clothing
and jewelry.
</P>
<P>
   ''We wanted to maintain a presence downtown,'' he said. ''Just
to be a thorn in their (city officials) side.''
</P>
<P>
   The Flynts closed two downtown Cincinnati stores after disputes
with the city over its sexually oriented business law.
</P>
<P>
   City Manager John Shirey was not pleased about the news.
</P>
<P>
   ''We can do what we always do, enforce city ordinances,'' he
said. ''But that doesn't occur until after they open.''
</P>
<P>
   The Flynts said the new store would comply with the city law
banning businesses from downtown if a ''significant or
substantial'' amount of the merchandise is sexually explicit.
</P>
