<HEADLINE> Shares Are Mixed in Europe  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LONDON (AP) -- European shares were mixed on Friday, as investors
continued to sell technology stocks and seek refuge in so-called
Old Economy shares.
</P>
<P>
   By the end of the European session, the Dow Jones Euro Stoxx
Index, which tracks companies in countries that joined the single
currency, was up 0.82 points, or 0.2 percent, at 441.07. The Dow
Jones Euro Stoxx 50 Index was down 2.4 points, at 5,249.6.
</P>
<P>
   The Dow Jones Stoxx Index of shares in European companies rose
2.44 points, or 0.6 percent, to 394.10, while the Dow Jones Stoxx
