</P>
<P>
   London's FTSE 100 closed 1.5 percent higher to 6,540.2, but
Paris's CAC-40 was down 0.4 percent at 6,286.05 and in Frankfurt
the Xetra DAX closed down 0.6 percent to 7,584.41.
</P>
<P>
   London's blue-chip index was supported by strong oil stocks and
a spread of old economy stocks. But technology stocks suffered in
response to Nasdaq's 4.0 percent slide Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   In Paris, technology, media and telecommunications stocks
dropped sharply in early trading and failed to maintain subsequent
gains.
</P>
<P>
   In Frankfurt, old economy stocks rallied and Siemens and
Deutsche Telekom recovered, but a profit warning from Ixos Software
pushed the DAX into negative territory.
</P>
