<DATE_TIME> 2000-03-31 16:44 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Men Said To Focus on White House Bid  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- Women are slightly less likely than men to be
interested in the presidential campaign and more likely to be
dissatisfied with politics, according to a four-month series of
polls released Friday.
</P>
<P>
   But women also are more likely than men to believe the election
will make a difference in their lives, according to the surveys for
Harvard University's Joan Shorenstein Center on the Press, Politics
and Public Policy.
</P>
<P>
   The telephone surveys of about 1,000 adults each, conducted from
Nov. 10 through March 26, found several areas of voter behavior
beyond the ''gender gap'' of women tending to vote for Democrats.
</P>
<P>
   Men and women, for example, have not paid equal attention to
this year's presidential race. On average, 37 percent of men said
they had thought about the campaign in the past day, compared with
32 percent of women.
</P>
<P>
   Women, meanwhile, were more likely than men to be dissatisfied
with politics and politicians. A survey conducted March 1-5 showed
that 76 percent of the women respondents on average felt that
politics is ''disgusting,'' compared with 67 percent of men on
average.
</P>
<P>
   However, more women than men feel that this election is an
important one. Along the course of the surveys, an average of 29
percent of women said the election would make a great deal of
difference in their lives, compared with an average of 25 percent
of men.
</P>
<P>
   In other areas, men and women had virtually the same opinions
and perceptions, the survey showed. For example, one-fifth of both
men and women say that people like them have a great deal or quite
a bit of influence on what the government does.
</P>
<P>
   Because some questions were asked only of some of the
respondents, the margin of error ranged from plus or minus 3
percentage points to 6 percentage points.
</P>
<P>
   ------
</P>
<P>
   On the Net: http://www.vanishingvoter.org
</P>
</TEXT>
