event at the request of Alamar Associates, a Washington-based
consulting firm that had set up three previous summits. Alamar said
the U.S. government has refused it permission to hold the gathering
in communist Cuba.
</P>
<P>
   Under the U.S. embargo against Cuba in place for nearly four
decades, the Treasury Department regulates spending on the island
by American firms and individuals.
