<HEADLINE> AP Financial News at 5:10 p.m. EST  </HEADLINE>
Friday, March 31, 2000
<TEXT>
<P>
   Nasdaq Up 114.70; Dow Ends Down 58.33
</P>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Technology stocks edged back from the brink
today, pulling the Nasdaq composite higher for the first time since
last Friday. Investors turned toward well-established computer
makers and networking companies, shunning newer Internet businesses
that were seen as riskier investments at the end of a volatile
week. The Nasdaq composite index rose 114.70 to close at 4,572.59.
In earlier trading, the Nasdaq had fallen as much as 76 points and
appeared to be in danger of extending its losing streak. Other
stock indicators were mixed. The Dow Jones industrial average gave
up solid early gains and closed down 58.33 at 10,921.92.
</P>
