<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Wichita St. Student Body Head Ousted  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WICHITA, Kan. (AP) -- Wichita State University students have
ousted their student body president, who came under fire after he
used his family's food stamps to stock a campus fund-raiser and
then took reimbursement from student funds.
</P>
<P>
   J. Alberto Fregoso lost a recall election held Wednesday and
Thursday, 269-209. He declined to comment afterward.
</P>
<P>
   The controversy began in November, when Fregoso, a 29-year-old
father of four, bought food for a Student Government Association
fund-raiser using his family's state food stamp card. He was later
reimbursed with a $90.54 check from the organization, which is
supported by student fees.
</P>
<P>
   No charges have been filed against him, but the state Department
of Social and Rehabilitation Services is investigating.
</P>
<P>
   Fregoso has said it was an honest mistake.
</P>
<P>
   ''It has been incredibly stressful,'' said Ernie Webb, a student
senator. ''I'm glad the students' voices were finally heard.''
</P>
<P>
   The student body president receives $8,580 as a state employee
for the yearlong term. Fregoso's term was not up until June 30.
</P>
<P>
   Fregoso could appeal to the university's Supreme Court but had
not done so Friday.
</P>
</TEXT>
