<HEADLINE> State office closes after fire  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ALBANY, N.Y. (AP) -- The second fire in a week in state
government's biggest office plaza left 390 state workers without a
place to work on Friday.
</P>
<P>
   The fire, attributed to carelessly discarded cleaning rags,
caused extensive damage to the 19th floor of Agency Building 3,
part of the Empire State Plaza in downtown Albany. It has been
termed accidental.
</P>
<P>
   No one was injured in the fire, which broke out at about 11 p.m.
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   A passerby on the street noticed smoke coming from the 19th
floor around 11 p.m., Albany fire officials said.
</P>
<P>
   On Tuesday, a small fire was reported in Building 4 of the same
plaza, also on the 19th floor. No injuries were reported in that
fire, either.
</P>
