<HEADLINE> Priest To Stand Trial in Bishop Case  </HEADLINE>
By WILL WEISSERT, Associated Press Writer
<TEXT>
<P>
   GUATEMALA CITY (AP) -- A judge refused Friday to dismiss charges
against a Roman Catholic priest accused in the 1998 slaying of
human rights campaigner Bishop Juan Gerardi, opening the way for a
trial in Guatemala's most infamous murder case.
</P>
<P>
   Judge Flor de Maria Garcia rejected a motion from the defense to
dismiss the arrest warrant against Mario Orantes. A date for his
trial has not yet been set.
</P>
<P>
   ''We have now completed all of the steps necessary to finally
bring criminal proceedings against the Reverend Orantes,'' said
Leopaldo Zeissig, who is heading the Public Ministry's
investigation of Orantes, who was the slain bishop's assistant.
</P>
<P>
   Head of the Roman Catholic Church's human rights office in
Guatemala, the 65-year-old Gerardi was bludgeoned to death with a
concrete block in April 1998 in the garage of the seminary where he
and Orantes lived and worked.
</P>
<P>
   His death came two days after he presented an encyclopedic
report that blamed the Guatemalan military for an overwhelming
majority of the 200,000 killings during Guatemala's 36-year civil
war. The conflict, which pitted leftist, mostly Indian guerrillas
against government forces ended in a 1996 peace agreement.
</P>
<P>
   Orantes, 41, is hospitalized with undisclosed back and nervous
system problems.
</P>
<P>
   Shortly after the slaying, authorities arrested Orantes, who
told police he was napping at the time of Gerardi's death but
stumbled upon his body in the seminary's garage.
</P>
<P>
   He spent seven months in prison on murder charges but was
released and allowed to travel to Houston to seek medical
treatment.
</P>
<P>
   Jose Toledo, Orantes chief attorney, said after the ruling that
his client was a scapegoat.
</P>
<P>
   ''I am absolutely, categorically sure that it was not Orantes
because I have looked at the evidence the prosecutors have
presented,'' he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-03-31-00 2223 </TRAILER>
